        <p>French naval surgeon and naturalist. Medical officer on board the <hi rend="italic">Coquille</hi>, 1822–5. Published the results of his zoological investigations made during the voyage. Taught botany at the naval medical school, Rochefort, 1829–31; appointed professor of pharmacy, 1831. Became the top-ranking navy pharmacist in 1835.</p></note>
